cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new class of deep learning prediction rules. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also mentions the possibility of using the new framework for image recognition tasks, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for network architecture optimization, which could place it under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
